{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "An anomaly detection model can be used to detect a fraudulent transaction or any highly imbalanced supervised tasks (Chandola et al. 2009).",
    "AEs can be used in supervised (Alsadhan 2023), unsupervised (Lopes et al. 2022), and semi-supervised (Akcay et al. 2018; Ruff et al. 2019) anomaly detection tasks.",
    "In supervised anomaly detection, AEs are trained on both normal and anomalous data.",
    "The AE is first trained on normal data to learn the underlying patterns and features of normal data.",
    "Then, the AE is fine-tuned on the combined normal and anomalous data to capture the difference between normal and anomalous data."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "An anomaly detection model can be used to detect a fraudulent transaction or any highly imbalanced supervised tasks (Chandola et al. 2009).",
    "AEs can be used in supervised (Alsadhan 2023), unsupervised (Lopes et al. 2022), and semi-supervised (Akcay et al. 2018; Ruff et al. 2019) anomaly detection tasks."
  ]
